<BR><BR>EXAMPLE 10
<BR><BR>The procedure of Example 2 is repeated except that step (2) of the example is replaced with the following.  The powder mixture from step (1) is granulated using minimal amounts of glycerine/water and processed into 3 mm diameter spheres by
mechanical extrusion and spheronization.  To accomplish this, the flexible mass is extruded from a Luwa Xtruda Extruder (Luwa Corporation Process Division), which produces a 3 mm diameter, continuous, cylindrical extrudate; this extrudate is then broken
into cylindrical pellets of 1:1.1 length-to-diameter ratio; and these pellets are then worked into spheres of 3 mm diameter by action of a Nica spheronizer and dried.
